Body:
BC-BUDGET-SPI 
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following
stories for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Tuesday, Jan. 11, and thereafter. If you have any questions, please
call Bob Schenet on the national-foreign desk at (206) 448-8158.

   SMUGGLED-ALIENS (Seattle) _ The rash of aliens being smuggled to
the West Coast from China turns deadly. Three of 18 stowaways in a
container ship that docked in Seattle Monday are found dead.

   By Scott Sunde. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)

   FBN-THIEL-COLUMN (Seattle) _ On the demise of the Seattle
Seahawks.

   By Art Thiel. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)

   AOL-NEXT (Seattle) _ With AOL joining with Time Warner,
Microsoft seems to have been one-upped by its rivals. But analysts
say more such mergers are likely.

   By Bruce Ramsey. (Story will move in the ``f'' category.)

   TV-TOUR (Pasadena, Calif.) _ Bits and pieces from the TV
critics' winter tour.

   By John Levesque. (Story has moved in the ``e'' category.)
